- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper evaluates the performance of different implementations of Reed Solomon codes for storage systems, which involves designing and analyzing control systems. 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper discusses the implementation and optimization of Reed Solomon codes for storage systems, which is relevant to the design and architecture of computer systems. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation): The paper discusses the use of polynomial realization of Reed Solomon codes, which involves symbolic computation techniques such as polynomial arithmetic.
